description:
About UsWe are a 100% remote company with just over 40 employees working across the globe every single day to build products that enrich peoples lives. We combine the simplicity and greatness of Apple products by creating utility and productivity apps that make peoples lives easier. Our portfolio contains Translate Now &amp; Calculator Air both the fastest-growing apps in their category. Our apps have been downloaded over 50 million times and received over 2 million ratings with an average of 4.6 stars.What are we hiring for?We are looking for a senior member of the iOS technical team for our Translation Studio.The Translation Studio comprises our translation suite of apps covering our Apple-featured and leading translator app by revenue in the US (last 12 months) TranslateNow and also TranslateNow - Keyboard and TranslateNow - Photo.When working in one of our Studio teams you will need to bring an entrepreneurial mindset. We do not just do what we are told - we do what makes sense make data-informed decisions and add value to our users alwaysYou will work with a close-knit team of (Director of Studios another senior member of the iOS technical team and 1x senior member of the product design team) - who will be tasked with delivering value to our users - measured via key metrics (e.g. our App Store Ranking revenue retention and so on). While you will be driving on the development side your responsibilities extend all the way as if the apps were your own  - we are all jointly accountable and jointly benefit for the success of delivering value to our users.What are we looking for?
An entrepreneurial spirit - You latch on fast to deliver value to your users and you are outspoken assertive and opinionated to make it happen;
Knowledge on bringing it all together - We may start small but we have big ambitions the ability to bring a growing team together collaborating and building a team environment that excites you every single day;
Passion drive and interest - We all love what we do we love apps we love the value we can provide to our users and we love staying on top of everything happening in the market both from a user perspective and technically;

Technical experience and ownership - You will be working on some of our biggest apps with a huge user base we need you to bring that confidence technically - but also you will be owning the apps as if they were your own - so be ready to:
demonstrate a desire and enjoyment in getting your hands dirty;
discuss and implement architecture/infrastructure-focussed decisions;
research discuss document and automate;
work on critical to the smallest bug fixes;
attend stand-ups complete grooming estimation peer reviews etc;
understand complex requirements;
delve into the data propose ideas and more.


Whats in for you?We offer a fully remote results-driven work style that enhances productivity and quality providing excellent work-life balance. We also have great opportunities to connect with our international team through coffee calls team meetings and hackathons.
Proven startup with significant ambitions;
Flexible work environment 100% remote;
Apple hardware environment;
USD350.00 Annual Home office set up;
Air Stipend 3000 USD/year paid over 12 monthly installments (so you can cover health insurance home office learning wellness etc);
USD200.00 Annual Meet a Team Member Stipend;
Air Academy;
Flexible PTO;
Retreats- Next year were off to Cancun üá≤üáΩüöÄ
RequirementsAre you passionate about building world-class software? Do you aspire to join an energetic team in a fast-growing startup to build and grow products at scale? So your desired skills and experience include:
Fluency in English spoken and written
6+ years of professional experience in iOS Development
6+ years of programming in Swift
Experience with Objective-C
iOS / iPadOS / Watch OS / macOS SDKs
Understanding of iOS Cocoa Touch Framework UIKit and SwiftUI
Understanding of SOLID principles
Experience working with CI/CD pipelines like Bitrise or Jenkins
Experience working with package managers like Cocoapods HomeBrew and SPM
Experience working with Jira (the team will be working Kanban)
Knowledge of Gitflow code reviews and processes
Understanding of App Store release process
